Docker file components:
    FROM <image>: This specifies the base image that the build will extend - Sets the base image for the Docker image
    LABEL: Adds metadata to the image ->> LABEL maintainer="venkat@gmail.com"
    RUN <command>: This instruction tells the builder to run the specified command - Executes the commands during the build process ->> RUN apt update && apt install
    CMD ["<command>","<arg1>"]:This instruction sets the default command a container using this image will run - Specifies the default command to run when container starts ->> CMD ["python","app.py"]
    ENTRYPOINT: Always runs as the main command of the container ->> ENTRYPOINT["python"]
    WORKDIR <path>: This instruction specifies the "working directory" or path in the image where files will be copied and command will be executed - Sets the working directory inside the container ->> WORKDIR/app
    COPY <host-path> <image-path>: This instruction tells the builder to copy files from the host and put them into the container image-Copies the files from local machine to container ->> COPY. /app
    ADD: Similar to COPY command but also supports URL download and tar extraction. ->> ADD app.tar.gz /app
    ENV <name> <value>:This instruction sets an environment variable that a running container will use Sets environment variables
    EXPOSE <port-number>: This instruction sets configuration on the image that indicates a port the image would like to expose - Documents the port the container listens on ->> EXPOSE 5000
    USER <user-or-uid>: This instruction sets the default user for all subsequent instructions- Sets the user for running commands ->> USER root
    VOLUME: Creates a mount point or attaches storage ->> VOLUME["/data"]
