Explain the difference between docker run and docker exec -it

    The difference is simpler than it first looks—one creates a container, the other enters an existing one.

    🔹 1. docker run

    👉 Creates + starts a new container
        docker run -it ubuntu bash

        What happens:
            Pulls image (if not present)
            Creates a new container
            Starts it
            Runs the command (bash)
            Attaches terminal (because of -it)

            👉 Every time you run this, you get a fresh container

    🔹 2. docker exec -it

            👉 Runs a command inside an already running container
                docker exec -it <container_id> bash

                What happens:
                    Uses an existing running container
                    Opens a new interactive terminal session inside it
                    Does NOT create a new container
        🔹 Key Difference (Core Idea)
        Feature	            docker run	                                  docker exec -it
        Container	        Creates new	                                  Uses existing
        State	            Fresh	                                      Keeps existing state
        Use case	        Start app / container	                      Debug / inspect running container
        Needs container?	No	                                          Yes (must be running)

🔹 Real-World Example
        Step 1: Start a container
        docker run -d --name myapp nginx

        👉 Now container is running in background

        Step 2: Enter it
        docker exec -it myapp bash

        👉 You’re now inside the same running container

    🔹 Important Insight

    ❌ Wrong thinking:

            "exec is same as run"

    ✅ Correct thinking:

        run = launch a new house
        exec = enter an already running house
🔹 When to Use What
    Use docker run:
        Starting a new service
        Running a one-time job
        Creating containers
    Use docker exec -it:
        Debugging issues
        Checking logs/files
        Running commands inside live container
🔹 Interview Answer (1-liner)

"docker run creates and starts a new container, while docker exec -it runs commands inside an already running container interactively."

